{
  "name": "The Fate System",
  "pages": [
    {
      "_id": "fate-overview",
      "name": "Overview",
      "type": "text",
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>Fate represents a character's luck, destiny, or divine favor. Characters\ncan spend Fate points to influence dice rolls, avoid death, or gain other\nbenefits. Fate is a limited resource that refreshes under specific\ncircumstances.</p>\n<p>See also: <a href=\"user-guide/skill-tests.md\">Skill Tests</a>, <a href=\"user-guide/item-trait.md\">Traits</a></p>\n"
      },
      "_key": "!journal.pages!39d52JG4fSyhU7cg.fate-overview"
    },
    {
      "_id": "fate-points",
      "name": "Fate Points",
      "type": "text",
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>Each character has a number of Fate points determined by their traits.\nFate points can be:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Spent</strong> to improve a test result or avoid a catastrophic outcome</li>\n<li><strong>Earned</strong> through gameplay milestones or GM awards</li>\n<li><strong>Refreshed</strong> at the start of certain time periods</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- TODO: Document exactly how Fate points are tracked on the character\n     sheet, where the current/maximum values are displayed, and how the\n     GM manages Fate point awards -->"
      },
      "_key": "!journal.pages!39d52JG4fSyhU7cg.fate-points"
    },
    {
      "_id": "fate-using",
      "name": "Using Fate",
      "type": "text",
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<h2>Fate Tests</h2>\n<p>A <strong>Fate test</strong> is a special roll that determines whether fate intervenes\non the character's behalf. Fate tests are typically triggered automatically\nwhen a character faces a life-threatening situation.</p>\n<!-- TODO: Document when Fate tests are triggered, how they're resolved,\n     and what happens on success vs. failure -->\n<h2>Spending Fate</h2>\n<p>Characters can voluntarily spend Fate points to:</p>\n<!-- TODO: Document the specific ways Fate can be spent — re-rolls,\n     result upgrades, death avoidance, etc. -->\n<!-- TODO: Document how many Fate points characters start with, how they\n     regenerate, and what options are available for spending them -->"
      },
      "_key": "!journal.pages!39d52JG4fSyhU7cg.fate-using"
    },
    {
      "_id": "fate-settings",
      "name": "Settings",
      "type": "text",
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>The <strong>Fate</strong> option in the system settings controls whether Fate is\ntracked automatically.</p>\n<p>See <a href=\"user-guide/settings.md\">Settings</a> for more configuration options.</p>\n"
      },
      "_key": "!journal.pages!39d52JG4fSyhU7cg.fate-settings"
    }
  ],
